venue.name: Starbucks
venue.header: According to the Foursquare community, this place is a 6.5 out of 10.
venue.explanation: We take into account visits and input from our community. You'll see a number on places based off of ratings and tips written by people like you.

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

pageInfo.description: Follow Starbucks on Foursquare to check in and earn great badges. Visit enough stores to become the envy of your friends with the Barista Badge.

items.text: Stop by often enough so that Delilah or Tina know you by name and start your drink order while you're at the back of the line.
There's a quite long communal table in the back, and good wireless internet access. There's also a sunporch for people-watching. One of the larger Starbucks I've seen in NY.
New management tries to cheat you out of your free refills.
Literally live here, can catch me sipping  an ice coffee with 2 pumps caramel accompanied by chocolate covered graham crackers, on the DaAILY.

sample.text: by far the worst Starbucks in NYC. the staff is loud, rude and...
